result.execSummary:
The defendant Alex A Moulton was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).
  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Defendant Alex A Moulton in court with attorney Mark H Bennett.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

BY THE COURT:  Withhold Sentence; 5 years Probation with conditions:
*Court Costs = $268.00 on each count

Defendant Alex A Moulton in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Court confirms the defendant's address.  Atty Gumz is here today but the defendant is not eligible for counsel.  Atty Gumz asks for an initial appearance date to be set.
Atty Hendee asks for a $10,000 cash bond with conditions.  Atty Hendee states that the defendant is possibly facing charges in three other counties.  Court advises the defendant of his right to an Attorney and gives options.  Defendant understands.  
Atty Gumz makes arguments and requests a $500 cash bail.  Atty Hendee requests the no contact and in addition no contact Grant Pulver.  Atty Gumz opposes the no contact with Mr. Pulver due to the defendant living with Mr. Moulton.   Court questions the State.  Atty Hendee answers why the no contact is requested.  
Atty Gumz responds.

  BY THE COURT:  Court sets a $2,500 cash bond with conditions:
*No contact with the co-defendant Dylan J Bartaczewicz
*No contact with Grant Pulver; if released, the defendant may return to the home one time with Law Enforcement to get his belongings.  Initial appearance scheduled for September 26, 2016 at 02:30 pm.
